1299:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/a76xx/a7677s.c ****  * success.  modem_command checks res_success before res_fail, so ":0\r\n"
1300:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/a76xx/a7677s.c ****  * is caught as success and any other "+CMQTTSTART:N" is caught by res_fail
1301:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/a76xx/a7677s.c ****  * (which is a substring match on "ERROR\r\n" — the modem always sends
1302:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/a76xx/a7677s.c ****  * "ERROR\r\n" on hard failures; for URC errcode failures we rely on timeout
1303:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/a76xx/a7677s.c ****  * since the modem sends OK + bad URC without an ERROR line, so the AT layer
1304:SynaptiX_FDK/components/modules/a76xx/a7677s.c ****  * will eventually time out and fire the callback with TIMEOUT). */
